â€¹ch sÃ¡Â»Â­ kh&aacute;c nhÃ†Â° tÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£ng vua L&ecirc; Th&aacute;i TÃ¡Â»â€¢, cÃ¡ÂºÂ§u Th&ecirc; H&uacute;c, th&aacute;p B&uacute;t, Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n B&agrave; KiÃ¡Â»â€¡u,... b&ecirc;n cÃ¡ÂºÂ¡nh nhÃ¡Â»Â¯ng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh kiÃ¡ÂºÂ¿n tr&uacute;c hiÃ¡Â»â€¡n Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¡i. To&agrave; nh&agrave; BÃ†Â°u Ã„â€˜iÃ¡Â»â€¡n vÃ¡Â»â€ºi th&aacute;p Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»â€œng hÃ¡Â»â€œ cÃ¡Â»â€¢ k&iacute;nh in b&oacute;ng hÃ¡Â»â€œ GÃ†Â°Ã†Â¡m Ã„â€˜&atilde; Ã„â€˜i v&agrave;o l&ograve;ng nhiÃ¡Â»ï¿½u ngÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»ï¿½i d&acirc;n H&agrave; NÃ¡Â»â„¢i.</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c8c8a03f71_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>CÃ¡ÂºÂ§u Th&ecirc; H&uacute;c dÃ¡ÂºÂ«n v&agrave;o Ã„ï¿½Ã¡Â»ï¿½n NgÃ¡Â»ï¿½c SÃ†Â¡n</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">NgÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»ï¿½i d&acirc;n H&agrave; NÃ¡Â»â„¢i sÃ¡Â»â€˜ng Ã¡Â»Å¸ khu vÃ¡Â»Â±c quanh hÃ¡Â»â€œ c&oacute; th&oacute;i quen ra Ã„â€˜&acirc;y tÃ¡ÂºÂ­p thÃ¡Â»Æ’ dÃ¡Â»Â¥c v&agrave;o s&aacute;ng sÃ¡Â»â€ºm, Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ·c biÃ¡Â»â€¡t l&agrave; v&agrave;o m&ugrave;a h&egrave;. HÃ¡Â»ï¿½ gÃ¡Â»ï¿½i c&aacute;c khu phÃ¡Â»â€˜ nÃ¡ÂºÂ±m quanh hÃ¡Â»â€œ l&agrave; BÃ¡Â»ï¿½ HÃ¡Â»â€œ.<br /><br />Th&aacute;p B&uacute;t (hay l&agrave; b&uacute;t th&aacute;p) nÃ¡ÂºÂ±m Ã¡Â»Å¸ cÃ¡ÂºÂ¡nh hÃ¡Â»â€œ, Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»â€˜i vÃ¡Â»â€ºi Ã„â€˜&agrave;i nghi&ecirc;n nÃ¡ÂºÂ±m Ã¡Â»Å¸ bÃ¡Â»ï¿½ hÃ¡Â»â€œ. MÃ¡Â»â€”i ng&agrave;y, b&oacute;ng cÃ¡Â»Â§a Th&aacute;p b&uacute;t ngÃ¡ÂºÂ£ xuÃ¡Â»â€˜ng chÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m mÃ¡Â»Â±c trong Ã„â€˜&agrave;i nghi&ecirc;n, tÃ¡ÂºÂ¡o th&agrave;nh mÃ¡Â»â„¢t biÃ¡Â»Æ’u tÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£ng rÃ¡ÂºÂ¥t Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¹p cho hÃ¡Â»ï¿½c vÃ¡ÂºÂ¥n: "Th&aacute;p B&uacute;t - Ã„â€˜&agrave;i nghi&ecirc;n - Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½ thÃ†Â¡ l&ecirc;n trÃ¡Â»ï¿½i xanh"<br /><br />Chu vi s&aacute;t bÃ¡Â»ï¿½ hÃ¡Â»â€œ l&agrave; khoÃ¡ÂºÂ£ng 1750m, c&ograve;n chu vi Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»ï¿½ng xe cÃ†Â¡ giÃ¡Â»â€ºi Ã„â€˜i v&ograve;ng quanh hÃ¡Â»â€œ l&agrave; khoÃ¡ÂºÂ£ng 2000m.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c881016a8d_large.jpg', 'active', 3, '11:52:33', 1, 'admin', '18:26:00', 1, 'admin', 1, 'admin', '11:54:59', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'vi_VN');
INSERT INTO news_article (article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, image_square, image_thumbnail, image_small, image_crop, image_medium, image_large, status, num_views, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name, updated_date, updated_user_id, updated_user_name, activate_user_id, activate_user_name, activate_date, allow_comment, num_comments, is_hot, ordering, show_date, sticky, language) VALUES (5, 1, 'Sa Pa', '', 'sa-pa', '<p>Sapa is a frontier town and capital of Sa Pa District in the L&agrave;o Cai province in northwest Vietnam. It is one of the main market towns in the area, where many ethnic minority groups such as H''mong, Dao and Tay live.</p>', '<p>Sa Pa District is located in Lao Cai Province, north-west Vietnam, and 350 km north-west of Hanoi, close to the border with China. The Hoang Lien Son range of mountains dominates the district, which is at the eastern extremity of the Himalayas. This range includes Vietnam''s highest mountain, Fan Si Pan, at a height of 3142m above sea level. The town of Sa Pa lies at an altitude of about 1600 m. The climate is moderate and rainy in summer (May&mdash;August), and foggy and cold with occasional snowfalls in winter.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Sa Pa town</em></p>\r\n<p>Sa Pa is a quiet mountain town and home to a great diversity of ethnic minority peoples. The total population of 36,000 consists mostly of minority groups. Besides the Kinh (Viet) people (15%) there are mainly 5 ethnic groups in Sapa: Hmong 52%, Dao 25%, Tay 5%, Giay 2% and a small number of Xa Pho. Approximately 7,000 live in Sapa, the other 36,000 being scattered in small communes throughout the district.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9de6e9139_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>View on the mountains from downtown Sapa</em></p>\r\n<p>Most of the ethnic minority people work their land on sloping terraces since the vast majority of the land is mountainous. Their staple foods are rice and corn. Rice, by its very nature of being a labour intensive crop, makes the daily fight for survival paramount. The unique climate in Sapa has a major influence on the ethnic minorities who live in the area. With sub-tropical summers, temperate winters and 160 days of mist annually, the influence on agricultural yields and health related issues are significant.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c9d36eeb3f_large.jpg', 'active', 3, '13:16:01', 1, 'admin', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'admin', '13:16:08', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 'en_US');
