nhiÃ¡Â»ï¿½u Ã„â€˜o&agrave;n theo lÃ¡Â»â€¹ch Ã„â€˜Ã„Æ’ng k&yacute;. C&aacute;c Ã„â€˜o&agrave;n rÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc kiÃ¡Â»â€¡u v&agrave; ch&acirc;n nhang tÃ¡Â»Â« c&aacute;c di t&iacute;ch thÃ¡Â»ï¿½ c&aacute;c danh nh&acirc;n thÃ¡Â»ï¿½i Ã„ï¿½inh - L&ecirc; sÃ¡ÂºÂ½ tham gia rÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc kiÃ¡Â»â€¡u vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ 2 Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n, hÃ¡ÂºÂ§u hÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t c&aacute;c Ã„â€˜o&agrave;n Ã¡Â»Å¸ cÃ¡Â»Â± ly xa phÃ¡ÂºÂ£i rÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc tr&ecirc;n xe lÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i tiÃ¡ÂºÂ¿n vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ Hoa LÃ†Â°. LÃ¡Â»â€¦ tÃ¡ÂºÂ¿ Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c tiÃ¡ÂºÂ¿n h&agrave;nh sau Ã„â€˜&oacute; cÃ¡ÂºÂ£ ban ng&agrave;y v&agrave; ban Ã„â€˜&ecirc;m Ã¡Â»Å¸ cÃ¡ÂºÂ£ Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n vua Ã„ï¿½inh v&agrave; vua L&ecirc; vÃ¡Â»â€ºi nÃ¡Â»â„¢i dung ca ngÃ¡Â»Â£i c&ocirc;ng Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»Â©c cÃ¡Â»Â§a hai vÃ¡Â»â€¹ vua, sen kÃ¡ÂºÂ½ Ã„â€˜&oacute; du kh&aacute;ch v&agrave;o thÃ¡ÂºÂ¯p hÃ†Â°Ã†Â¡ng tÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Å¸ng niÃ¡Â»â€¡m. Tham gia lÃ¡Â»â€¦ tÃ¡ÂºÂ¿ c&oacute; nhiÃ¡Â»ï¿½u Ã„â€˜o&agrave;n trong v&ugrave;ng.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccee363d4b_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>LÃ¡Â»â€¦ tÃ¡ÂºÂ¿ cÃ¡Â»â€¢ truyÃ¡Â»ï¿½n tÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n Vua Ã„ï¿½inh Ti&ecirc;n Ho&agrave;ng</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">M&agrave;n s&acirc;n khÃ¡ÂºÂ¥u h&oacute;a: Ã„ï¿½&acirc;y l&agrave; m&agrave;n diÃ¡Â»â€¦n s&acirc;n khÃ¡ÂºÂ¥u Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã†Â¡ng Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¡i Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»Æ’ khai mÃ¡ÂºÂ¡c lÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i v&agrave; truyÃ¡Â»ï¿½n h&igrave;nh trÃ¡Â»Â±c tiÃ¡ÂºÂ¿p. Sau lÃ¡Â»ï¿½i diÃ¡Â»â€¦n vÃ„Æ’n khai mÃ¡ÂºÂ¡c l&agrave; m&agrave;n trÃ¡Â»â€˜ng hÃ¡Â»â„¢i Hoa LÃ†Â°, c&aacute;c m&agrave;n diÃ¡Â»â€¦n t&aacute;i hiÃ¡Â»â€¡n lÃ¡Â»â€¹ch sÃ¡Â»Â­ trÃ¡Â»ï¿½ng Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¡i diÃ¡Â»â€¦n ra tÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i kinh Ã„â€˜&ocirc; Hoa LÃ†Â° xÃ†Â°a nhÃ†Â°: sÃ¡Â»Â± kiÃ¡Â»â€¡n l&ecirc;n ng&ocirc;i ho&agrave;ng Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¿ cÃ¡Â»Â§a Ã„ï¿½inh BÃ¡Â»â„¢ LÃ„Â©nh v&agrave; L&ecirc; Ho&agrave;n; Ã„â€˜&aacute;nh thÃ¡ÂºÂ¯ng giÃ¡ÂºÂ·c TÃ¡Â»â€˜ng; dÃ¡Â»ï¿½i Ã„â€˜&ocirc; vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ ThÃ„Æ’ng Long v&agrave; kÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t th&uacute;c l&agrave; m&agrave;n thÃ¡ÂºÂ£ rÃ¡Â»â€œng bay l&ecirc;n cho tÃ¡Â»â€ºi hÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t buÃ¡Â»â€¢i s&aacute;ng khai mÃ¡ÂºÂ¡c.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_large.jpg', 'active', 2, '16:42:26', 1, 'admin', '17:01:33', 1, 'admin', 1, 'admin', '16:42:49', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'vi_VN');
INSERT INTO news_article (article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, image_square, image_thumbnail, image_small, image_crop, image_medium, image_large, status, num_views, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name, updated_date, updated_user_id, updated_user_name, activate_user_id, activate_user_name, activate_date, allow_comment, num_comments, is_hot, ordering, show_date, sticky, language) VALUES (41, 8, 'CÃ†Â¡m tÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m', '', 'com-tam', '<p style="text-align: justify;">CÃ†Â¡m tÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m in Vietnamese is cooked rice from fractured rice grains. TÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m refers to the broken rice grains while cÃ†Â¡m refers to cooked rice.<br /><br /></p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It is usually served with grilled pork (either ribs or shredded) plus a Vietnamese dish called b&igrave; (thinly shredded pork mixed with cooked and thinly shredded pork skin) over broken rice. The rice and meat are served with various greens and pickled vegetables, along with a prawn paste cake, trÃ¡Â»Â©ng hÃ¡ÂºÂ¥p (baked egg), and grilled prawns. Typically restaurants will serve this popular combination rice plate with a small bowl of nÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc chÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m, as well as a small bowl of soup broth (canh) with garlic chives (to cleanse the throat).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce1fb72ae2_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>CÃ†Â¡m tÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m with grilled pork, shredded pork, pork skin, fried egg, pork meatloaf, pickled carrot, and sliced cucumber</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span id="Broken_Rice" class="mw-headline">Broken Rice</span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Some rice grains break in the transport and processing of the rice from the field to the pot. Machinery is available to separate the broken grains from the whole grains. Broken rice may or may not have lower fiber and nutrient content, but generally has a similar energy content to intact rice.<br /><br />The broken varieties are often less expensive, so are preferred by poorer consumers or used as raw material (such as in beer brewing). ue to the different size and shape of the grains, broken rice has a different texture from "unbroken" rice. Some chefs and consumers may prefer the qualities of broken rice for certain dishes.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ce2687f4e4_large.jpg', 'active', 1, '18:07:28', 1, 'admin', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'admin', '18:07:36', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO news_article (article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, image_square, image_thumbnail, image_small, image_crop, image_medium, image_large, status, num_views, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name, updated_date, updated_user_id, updated_user_name, activate_user_id, activate_user_name, activate_date, allow_comment, num_comments, is_hot, ordering, show_date, sticky, language) VALUES (30, 3, 'Hoa Lu ancient capital festival', '', 'hoa-lu-ancient-capital-festival', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Hoa Lu ancient capital Festival opened in the spring.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Start a ceremony at the Yellow River Long procession of the temple 2 Kings. Group stage near the procession of King Dinh Tien Hoang Temple. There will be many games in the Assembly. Hoa Lu Festival described the history of Vietnam from 968 to 1010 with many changes.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccee363d4b_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Hoa Lu ancient capital Festival&nbsp; </em></p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_large.jpg', 'active', 2, '17:00:21', 1, 'admin', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'admin', '17:00:29', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO news_article (article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, image_square, image_thumbnail, image_small, image_crop, image_medium, image_large, status, num_views, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name, updated_date, updated_user_id, updated_user_name, activate_user_id, activate_user_name, activate_date, allow_comment, num_comments, is_hot, ordering, show_date, sticky, language) VALUES (31, 3, 'Lantern Festival', '', 'lantern-festival', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The Lantern Festival or "TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t ThÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£ng Nguy&ecirc;n" or "TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Nguy&ecirc;n Ti&ecirc;u"(Vietnamese: TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Nguy&ecirc;n ti&ecirc;u) in Vietnam; is a festival celebrated on the fifteenth day of the first month in the lunar year in the Chinese calendar, the last day of the Lunar Chinese New Year celebration.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It is not to be confused with the Mid-Autumn Festival, which is sometimes also known as the "Lantern Festival" in locations such as Singapore and Malaysia. During the Lantern Festival, children go out at night to temples carrying paper lanterns and solve riddles on the lanterns. It officially ends the Chinese New Year celebrations.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Lantern Festival celebration in Shijiazhuang.</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In ancient times, the lanterns were fairly simple, for only the emperor and noblemen had large ornate ones; in modern times, lanterns have been embellished with many complex designs. For example, lanterns are now often made in shapes of animals.<br /><br />The Lantern Festival is also known as the Little New Year since it marks the end of the series of celebrations starting from the Chinese New Year.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59084397_crop.JPG" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Year 2008 Taiwan Lantern Festival in Tainan, Taiwan.</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In some region and countries, this festival is also regarded as the Chinese version of St. Valentine''s Day, a day celebrating love and affection between lovers in Chinese tradition and culture.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_square.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_thumbnail.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_small.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_crop.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_medium.jpg', 'http://localhost/amancms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_large.jpg', 'active', 3, '17:14:03', 1, 'admin', '17:33:02', 1, 'admin', 1, 'admin', '17:14:09', 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'en_US');
