e;ng K&ecirc;nh are not rolls, but just rice sheets eaten with chÃ¡ÂºÂ£ lÃ¡Â»Â¥a, fried shallots, or prawns; see the article B&aacute;nh cuÃ¡Â»â€˜n in the Vietnamese Wikipedia.<br /><br />A similar Chinese dish is the Cantonese dish coeng4 fan2 (Ã¨â€šÂ Ã§Â²â€°; pinyin: ch&aacute;ngfÃ„â€ºn), usually translated into English as "steamed rice roll" or "rice noodle roll," which is a form of dim sum.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '16:02:14', 1, 'admin');
